'''Saikan''' (斎館, ''Saikan'') is a sprawling temple lodging atop [[Mt. Haguro]] (羽黒山 ''Haguro-san''), part of the [[Three Mountains of Dewa]] (出羽三山 ''Dewa Sanzan'') in Japan.  

Saikan connects directly to the main temple of the complex through a long [[passageway]] that climbs further up the mountain.  Elaborate ''Gohonbo Bassho-zen'' meals are served to visitors.  Traditionally, it is reached by climbing up 2,466 stone steps up the side of the mountain, but it can also be reached by car or bus.

