{{Infobox religious building | name = {{Nihongo|'''Saikan'''|斎館}} | image = Saikan1.jpg | caption = A twisting hallway in Saikan. | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|38.703364|139.979944|format=dms|display=title,inline|type:landmark_region:JP_scale:10000}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} '''Saikan''' (斎館, ''Saikan'') is a sprawling temple lodging atop [[Mount Haguro|Mt. Haguro]] (羽黒山 ''Haguro-san''), part of the [[Three Mountains of Dewa]] (出羽三山 ''Dewa Sanzan'') in [[Yamagata Prefecture]], [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite book |last=岩鼻通明 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XPczAAAAMAAJ&newbks=0&hl=en |title=出羽三山信仰の歴史地理学的研究 |date=1992 |publisher=名著出版 |isbn=978-4-626-01430-6 |pages=3 |language=ja}}</ref> It was previously known as {{Nihongo3||華蔵院|Kezō-in}}.<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DgZPAQAAMAAJ&newbks=0&hl=en |title=日本の美術 |date=2005 |publisher=至文堂 |pages=84 |language=ja}}</ref>
